sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as maas-default-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS Terminate
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant Authorino<br/>mTLS (mesh)
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant PayloadProc as payload-processing<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant Model as Model Endpoint<br/>(KServe / External)
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant ExtProvider as External LLM Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Client,Model: Flow 1: Model Inference via API Key
        Client->>Gateway: POST /{ns}/{model}/v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-* API key<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS Terminate
        Gateway->>Authorino: AuthN/AuthZ evaluation<br/>mTLS (mesh-internal)
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>HTTP/8080 (NetworkPolicy restricted)
        MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: SELECT key hash<br/>SHA-256 constant-time compare
        PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key valid + metadata
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: 200 OK (user identity)
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select<br/>HTTP/8080 (NetworkPolicy restricted)
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Selected subscription + rate limit tier
        Authorino-->>Gateway: AuthZ result (allow + headers)
        Gateway->>PayloadProc: ext_proc request processing<br/>gRPC/9004 TLS (SIMPLE)
        Note over PayloadProc: Plugins execute sequentially:<br/>1. model-extractor (body → header)<br/>2. model-provider-resolver<br/>3. api-translation<br/>4. apikey-injection
        PayloadProc-->>Gateway: Modified request (credentials injected)
        Gateway->>Model: Forward inference request<br/>HTTPS/443
        Model-->>Gateway: Inference response
        Gateway->>PayloadProc: ext_proc response processing
        PayloadProc-->>Gateway: Translated response
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>HTTPS/443
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 2: API Key Creation
        Client->>Gateway: POST /maas-api/v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: Bearer OpenShift token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS Terminate
        Gateway->>Authorino: AuthN evaluation<br/>mTLS (mesh-internal)
        Authorino->>Authorino: K8s TokenReview<br/>HTTPS/6443
        Authorino-->>Gateway: AuthZ result (X-MaaS-Username/Group headers)
        Gateway->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>HTTP/8080 + identity headers
        MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: INSERT key hash<br/>(SHA-256, show-once pattern)
        PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Stored
        MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: 201 Created + plaintext key<br/>(shown once, never stored)
        Gateway-->>Client: API key response
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Client,ExtProvider: Flow 3: External Model Routing
        Client->>Gateway: POST /{ns}/{external-model}/*<br/>Auth: Bearer token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS Terminate
        Gateway->>Authorino: AuthN/AuthZ (same as Flow 1)
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Authorized
        Gateway->>PayloadProc: ext_proc processing<br/>gRPC/9004 TLS (SIMPLE)
        Note over PayloadProc: model-provider-resolver:<br/>resolves to external endpoint<br/>apikey-injection:<br/>injects provider API key from Secret
        PayloadProc-->>Gateway: Request with provider credentials
        Gateway->>ExtProvider: Forward via ServiceEntry<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS (SIMPLE, DestinationRule)<br/>Auth: Provider API Key (injected header)
        ExtProvider-->>Gateway: Provider response
        Gateway->>PayloadProc: ext_proc response translation
        PayloadProc-->>Gateway: Translated to unified format
        Gateway-->>Client: Unified JSON response
    end
